(537, 1, '2019-11-27 10:34:25', '2019-11-27 10:34:25', '', 'counter-strike-source-m4a1-silver-e1478601938395', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'counter-strike-source-m4a1-silver-e1478601938395', '', '', '2019-11-27 10:51:43', '2019-11-27 10:51:43', '', 300, 'http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/counter-strike-source-m4a1-silver-e1478601938395.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(477, 1, '2016-11-08 10:35:23', '2016-11-08 10:35:23', 'Hello everyone to this new post,\r\n\r\nToday I will deal about Profesionalism, especially in the creative industry. If you have already work in a company, this word won\'t be strange for you, but for most of student they can\'t define Professionalism, so I want to show you on image what is the profesionalism :\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_471\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"770\"]<a href=\"https://www.peterstark.com/quotes/professionalism-workplace/\"><img class=\"wp-image-471\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/project/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/professionalism_1000-1.jpg\" width=\"770\" height=\"479\" /></a> - This guy seems professional[/caption]\r\n\r\nPersonaly, the first word in mind when I pronounce \"Professionalism\" are : reliable, discipline, serving, competent. I think I will define a professional as a person who will bring what his customer desire, or even more, in the best way.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Why do I need to be professional ?</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you need to work in a important company, you can\'t go to work and want to be yourself, because once you are yourself you are  naturally unprofessional.\r\nIn order to work in good terms and in the good way you need to adopt professional codes, which will depends of your field.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Identify a professional person</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_473\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://ethicalsystems.org/content/professionalism_and_ethics\"><img class=\"wp-image-473 size-full\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/project/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/ProfessionalCircles.jpg\" alt=\"professionalcircles\" width=\"300\" height=\"268\" /></a> - Professionalism Diagram[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI have found this image on one of my source, and I think it is a good diagram to define how you can begin a professional.\r\n\r\nWe can see that the professionalism is a melt beetween : behaviour, skills, knowledge.\r\n\r\nObviously if you want to provide a good work to your customers you shoud have a decent skillset and knowledge, depending on your field.\r\n\r\nAlthough in my opinion I believe that behaviour is what will be differencing you as a professional and from your teammates. Because, theoretically you will have an equivalent level in technicals skills due to the fact that you are working on the same field. It will impact your communication and  your role wihin the group.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Professionalism in the creative industry</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_474\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-474 size-full\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/project/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Robots-in-Suits.jpg\" alt=\"robots-in-suits\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\" /> - Robots in suits[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFirst of all, to be a professional you must respect the codes of your field.\r\n\r\nWhereas in buisness, restoration or even in some school you must wear a kind of uniform to work. In the creative industry, I can  say that it is more creative, there is not a defined clothing code !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHowever for the work providden by developper the professionalism is a really important. When you are working in a company, you probably won\'t be alone on your project, that\'s why communication will be very important.\r\n\r\nAlthought, there is not only the oral communication, as a developper your codes must be first of all reliable and understandable by any others developpers. They should be able to understand your codes, mainly because a computing project is updated permanently and when someone would like to help you or, even better fill your work because you left the company, in order to continue the development.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAs well as you must respect a standard developping method to be understandable by anyone and communicate around your project. I believe that the third rules which will make you a professional is to respect the deadlines and to keep update of important news in your fields.\r\n\r\nFor example, as a professional I should return this blog today with this post !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span>\r\n\r\nGlobal informations, from ccSkills - <a href=\"https://ccskills.org.uk/careers/blog/being-a-creative-professional\" target=\"_blank\">Being a creative professional</a>\r\n\r\nGlobal informations, from the context of things\'s Blog - <a href=\"http://thecontextofthings.com/2016/03/07/professionalism-in-the-workplace/\" target=\"_blank\">Professionalism in the workplace</a>\r\n\r\nEthic, from ethical systems - <a href=\"http://ethicalsystems.org/content/professionalism_and_ethics\" target=\"_blank\">Professionalsim and ethics</a>\r\n\r\nTips to become a professional, from tech republic\'s Blog - <a href=\"http://www.techrepublic.com/blog/10-things/10-things-that-define-a-true-professional/\" target=\"_blank\">10 things that define a true professional</a>', 'Does the concept of professionalism apply to the creative industries ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '302-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-08 10:35:23', '2016-11-08 10:35:23', '', 302, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/project/blog/302-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(281, 1, '2016-09-23 22:00:59', '2016-09-23 20:00:59', '', 'Home', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'home', '', '', '2016-11-07 18:49:37', '2016-11-07 18:49:37', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/blog/2016/09/23/home/', 1, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(466, 1, '2016-11-07 19:34:47', '2016-11-07 19:34:47', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-319 aligncenter\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/project/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/mmm.jpg\" alt=\"welcome\" width=\"275\" height=\"183\" />\r\n\r\nHey, my name is Vincent, I am a 20 years old french student. I am currently studying Game Development in the University of the West of Scotland (UWS), and I wish you the welcome on my blog !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #993366; text-decoration: underline;\">About me\r\n</span></span></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"wp-image-320 alignleft\" src=\"http://127.0.0.1/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_20160924_161106-2.jpg\" alt=\"img_20160924_161106-2\" width=\"504\" height=\"283\" /> For 8 years, computing and video games have taken an important part on my free time. First of all, I have started as a self-educated and I did many projects to discover deeper the computing field.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">That\'s why, I decided to continue my studies in a first time in Electrical Engineering &amp; Industrial Computing during 2 years, in order to discover fields like automations, electronic, embeded computing which were fields that interested myself.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Finaly, I decided to forward in the computing. Instead of chose directly a french engineering school, I have prefered to take this year in a foreign country, in order to improve my english which is a very important skill in this field and also in the profesional world.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Moreover, I believe that this experience to discover an other culture, way of work, lifestyle, and also one of the interesting specifities of computing (Game Development) is a great opportunity\r\nfor me. Furthermore, I am sure about that this experience will help in my project of study after this year.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #993366; text-decoration: underline;\">About the blog</span></span></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis blog has been designed to cover various topics associated with ethical and professional aspects of the creative industries, In a first time, I will deal with subjects submitted during the Creative Technology Profesionalism course as creative industries, game design and related subjects.\r\nMoreover, in the future, I would like to publish other topics close to this fields !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFeel free to add me on your social account !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '264-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-07 19:34:47', '2016-11-07 19:34:47', '', 264, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/project/blog/264-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(351, 1, '2016-10-01 15:38:51', '2016-10-01 13:38:51', 'blablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablabla\r\n\r\nblablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablablabla\r\n\r\nblablablablablablablablablablablablablablablabla', 'What makes a good portfolio or showreel ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '275-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-01 15:38:51', '2016-10-01 13:38:51', '', 275, 'http://localhost/blog/275-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
