erstandable by anyone and communicate around your project. I believe that the third rules which will make you a professional is to respect the deadlines and to keep update of important news in your fields.\r\n\r\nFor example, as a professional I should return this blog today with this post !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span>\r\n\r\nGlobal informations, from ccSkills - <a href=\"https://ccskills.org.uk/careers/blog/being-a-creative-professional\" target=\"_blank\">Being a creative professional</a>\r\n\r\nGlobal informations, from the context of things\'s Blog - <a href=\"http://thecontextofthings.com/2016/03/07/professionalism-in-the-workplace/\" target=\"_blank\">Professionalism in the workplace</a>\r\n\r\nEthic, from ethical systems - <a href=\"http://ethicalsystems.org/content/professionalism_and_ethics\" target=\"_blank\">Professionalsim and ethics</a>\r\n\r\nTips to become a professional, from tech republic\'s Blog - <a href=\"http://www.techrepublic.com/blog/10-things/10-things-that-define-a-true-professional/\" target=\"_blank\">10 things that define a true professional</a>', 'Does the concept of professionalism apply to the creative industries ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '302-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-11-08 10:36:00', '2016-11-08 10:36:00', '', 302, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/project/blog/302-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
