(298, 1, '2016-10-03 13:09:33', '2016-10-03 12:09:33', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hello everyone and welcome for a new post this week,</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This week I will study the question of freelancing, I will deal about pros &amp; cons and give you my opinion about it. Is it a good choice of career ?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Basically we can say that freelancing is being a self-employe, that provide services to multiples customers. Be his own boss and work for the most part of the time alone, his a choice of career.</p>\n\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_523\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"500\"]<img class=\"wp-image-523 size-full\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/freelance3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"391\" /> A choice of career[/caption]\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As you may know, the freelancing in the EU is in good health, this numbers from the IPA are one more proof !</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #808080;\">\"Independent professionals in the EU grew from 6.2 million in 2004 to 8.9 million in 2013.The <a href=\"http://www.ipa.co.uk/page/ipa-agency-census#.V_eaeCgrI2w\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">IPA\'s 2014 Agency Census</a></span> <span style=\"color: #808080;\">revealed creative roles account for 41.8% of freelance jobs for member agencies.\"\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span> CampaignLive -</span> <a href=\"http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/1346999/why-creative-industries-embracing-freelance-economy#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">why creative industries embracing freelance economy</a></p>\n\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_524\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1024\"]<img class=\"wp-image-524 size-full\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/freelance4-1024x420.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"420\" /> What people believe about freelancing[/caption]\n<ul>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">One of the most interesting advantage for freelancer, is as you work alone, you are only dependant of the customer\'s order. You  can manage as you want your time during the week.Moreover, you <span style=\"color: #000000;\">work for you because <em>you </em>are the boss here, you choose your contract with your customers.\n</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">The second major advantage is that you can choose your customers, it will able you to developp your network.</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Furthermore due to the differentes orders you won\'t make the same thing all the time and you will permanently improve a variety of skills.</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">As you work alone you are more pay than in a traditional company (more fees)</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With already this point of view with the advantages, you trust in a dream job, but there are also cons, like in all job.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Cons :</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">As you depend of your network\'s order, you must build and maitain a decent network in order to work during all the year and get your money, there is no job security it is very important to notice that !</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">You are not alone on the freelancer market. Remember the previous statistic, it will be a real contest between freelancer for interesting call, and there is many website to find orders (freelancer.co.uk , freelanceuk.com,  peopleperhour.com, etc)</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">You will probably work more than a traditionnal job because as a boss you must provide papers for the administration</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Lonely...</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>My own point of view :</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As you have maybe guess during this article I won\'t do a freelance, but it can be a good choice of career and the road to success in the creative industry.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">It is pretty interesting thing to be in charge and manage his own time and skill to respond at customer\'s orders. I believe that it is a great experience, but until you have a decent network it is not a reliable situation.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So I will recomend to start a freelance when you get the network or when you have time and don\'t need a reliable situation (for your family for example).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I believe that it can be a great experience to do few years in freelancing before to comeback on the traditional work, because it will bring you another point of view of work than you colleague, and it is always interesting to have differents experiences.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>How succeed as a freelancer  in the creative industry?</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I think in one word we can define how succeed : <strong>Professionalism</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you provide a good work as the customer expect and you are aware about your network you will be an happy and successfull creative freelancer !</p>\n\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_522\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"580\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-522\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/freelance2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"580\" height=\"349\" /> Road to success[/caption]\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Statistics, from Campaign - <a href=\"http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/1346999/why-creative-industries-embracing-freelance-economy#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Why creative industries embracing freelance economy</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">General informations, from CreativeSkillset - <a href=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/working-in-the-creative-industries-is-freelancing-the-road-to-success/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">What\'s it like to work in the creative industries</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Personal view, from FastoCreate - <a href=\"https://www.fastcocreate.com/1681611/how-to-be-a-happy-and-successful-creative-freelancer-or-work-with-one\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">How to be a happy and successful creative freelancer or work with one</a></p>', 'Working in the creative industries: is freelancing the road to success ?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'working-in-the-creative-industries-is-freelancing-the-road-to-success', '', '', '2019-11-27 11:04:06', '2019-11-27 11:04:06', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/blog/?p=298', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(299, 1, '2016-09-25 19:19:33', '2016-09-25 17:19:33', 'NA', 'Working in the creative industries: is freelancing the road to success ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '298-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-09-25 19:19:33', '2016-09-25 17:19:33', '', 298, 'http://127.0.0.1/blog/2016/09/25/298-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(300, 1, '2016-09-25 23:08:46', '2016-09-25 21:08:46', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hello everyone to my second post.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In this new post, I will in a first time deal about the Intelectual Property (IP) and then we will focusing more on IP rights in the creative industry.</p>\n\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_534\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"wp-image-534 size-medium\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/intellectual-property-1024x886-300x260.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"260\" /> It was your idea ?[/caption]\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">First of all, let\'s introduce a short definition of IP rights from the<a href=\"http://www.wipo.int/edocs/pubdocs/en/intproperty/450/wipo_pub_450.pdf\"> World Intellectual Property Organization  (WIPO)</a> :</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #999999;\">\n\"Intellectual property refers to creations of the mind: inventions; literary and artistic works; and symbols, names and images used in commerce. Intellectual property is divided into two categories: Industrial property and Copyright\"</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In this quote, the WIPO define the IP to all kind of creations of the mind, it can be a right on a car model (industrial property) as well as a music (copyright), so it can be applied at a wide range of industry.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The aim of IP rights are like any other property right : They allow creators, or owners, of patents, trademarks or copyrighted works to prevent from a exploitation of the invention by a person or a company.</p>\n\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_535\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"480\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-535\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/hqdefault-1-e1478601816953.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"480\" height=\"272\" /> Youtube - Copyright claim[/caption]\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-536 size-medium\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Microsoft-Office-VS-LibreOffice-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\nThis right is recognized  since 1883 and it has been established in order to give at the creator the benefit from their own work or investment in a creation. It able to the inventor to sell his rights, deliver licences (you pay for a service) or even to get royalties !\nWhereas at the opposite there are also open source creations which will avoid this righst and provide this services free for you.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">However, even if you are the author or creator of a new creation, you are not obviously the owner !\nFor example if I create a new ingenious game mechanic, if I work for a game development company, this company will be the owner of the right. So we can say that the IP rights able to prevent also company from their own employee.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Now I will deal more in details with the copyright since it will more interest us in the creative industry. The copyright covers creative fields as music, movies, art, web content, photography and others. This right is automatically obtained when you write: the copyright symbol, your name and the year on a original creation and it will protect your work in your country but also at the international. Moreover you can assert your right up to 70 years after you died (<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/copyright/how-long-copyright-lasts\">depending of the kind of creations</a>), that\'s how if you are the son of Mickael Jackson you will  still <a href=\"https://johnsonsrambler.wordpress.com/2010/04/13/a-deeper-look-at-how-much-musicians-make-online/\">receive money from his creation </a>!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In my opinion, I believe that in the creative industry the copyright is a means to push the inovation. Creativity is what will able you to overcome the current limits and design a new concept. In this way, you will probably pass this limit and maybe create an awesome creation which will maybe become the new reference.</p>\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-537 size-full\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/counter-strike-source-m4a1-silver-e1478601938395.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"244\" />\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Even if sometimes the copyright of other will cost or block you in your project, you can always find a new way to do it. I remember an old version of Counter Strike (Source) in which Valve hadn\'t the rights on weapon\'s name yet. So they decided to \"create\" they own weapons which were just similar to the real weapons and create names (Maverick M4A1 Carabine instead of M4A1), smart ?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To conclude I will say that in the creative industry and more usually in all industry the Intelectual Property rights able to overcome the current limit. Even if it will be interesting I i think that a world with only open source invention without IP rights is not reliable for the invention. I believe that it will be the death of innovation because we will all adopt the same technology, so yes there is bad and good on IP rights but it is necessary to prevent the work provided and for the innovation !</p>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-538\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Dessin_-_01-1024x750.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"750\" />\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span>\n\nGlobal informations, from Wipo (World Intellectual Property Organization) <a href=\"http://www.wipo.int/edocs/pubdocs/en/intproperty/450/wipo_pub_450.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">- What is intelectual property</a>\n\nGlobal information, from Innovation policy platform <a href=\"https://www.innovationpolicyplatform.org/content/ip-and-creative-industries\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"> IP and creative industry</a>\n\nCopyright/Copyleft, from visionmobile blog <a href=\"https://www.visionmobile.com/blog/2011/03/the-open-source-trials-hanging-in-the-legal-balance-of-copyright-and-copyleft\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"> The open source trials hanging in the legal balance of copyright and copyleft</a>\n\nCopyright in the UK, from the UK government <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/copyright/overview\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"> How copyright protects your work</a>\n\nMusic royalties, from  Johnsons Rambler blog <a href=\"https://johnsonsrambler.wordpress.com/2010/04/13/a-deeper-look-at-how-much-musicians-make-online/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"> A deeper look at how much musicians make online</a>', 'Intelectual Property rights and their importance in the creative industries', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ip-rights-and-their-importance-in-the-creative-industries', '', '\nhttps://johnsonsrambler.wordpress.com/2010/04/13/a-deeper-look-at-how-much-musicians-make-online/', '2019-11-27 11:04:57', '2019-11-27 11:04:57', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/blog/?p=300', 0, 'post', '', 0),
