(302, 1, '2016-10-07 14:12:26', '2016-10-07 13:12:26', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hello everyone to this new post,</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Today I will deal about Profesionalism, especially in the creative industry. If you have already work in a company, this word won\'t be strange for you, but for most of student they can\'t define Professionalism, so I want to show you on image what is the profesionalism :</p>\n\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_531\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1000\"]<img class=\"wp-image-531 size-full\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/professionalism_1000-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"622\" /> This guy seems professional[/caption]\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Personaly, the first word in mind when I pronounce \"Professionalism\" are : reliable, discipline, serving, competent. I think I will define a professional as a person who will bring what his customer desire, or even more, in the best way.</p>\n<strong>Why do I need to be professional ?</strong>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you need to work in a important company, you can\'t go to work and want to be yourself, because once you are yourself you are  naturally unprofessional.\nIn order to work in good terms and in the good way you need to adopt professional codes, which will depends of your field.</p>\n<strong>Identify a professional person</strong>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_532\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"wp-image-532 size-full\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/ProfessionalCircles.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"268\" /> Professionalism Diagram[/caption]\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I have found this image on one of my source, and I think it is a good diagram to define how you can begin a professional.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We can see that the professionalism is a melt beetween : behaviour, skills, knowledge.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Obviously if you want to provide a good work to your customers you shoud have a decent skillset and knowledge, depending on your field.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although in my opinion I believe that behaviour is what will be differencing you as a professional and from your teammates. Because, theoretically you will have an equivalent level in technicals skills due to the fact that you are working on the same field. It will impact your communication and  your role wihin the group.</p>\n<strong>Professionalism in the creative industry</strong>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_533\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-533 size-full\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Robots-in-Suits.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\" /> Robots in suits[/caption]\n\nFirst of all, to be a professional you must respect the codes of your field.\n\nWhereas in buisness, restoration or even in some school you must wear a kind of uniform to work. In the creative industry, I can  say that it is more creative, there is not a defined clothing code !\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">However for the work providden by developper the professionalism is a really important. When you are working in a company, you probably won\'t be alone on your project, that\'s why communication will be very important.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Althought, there is not only the oral communication, as a developper your codes must be first of all reliable and understandable by any others developpers. They should be able to understand your codes, mainly because a computing project is updated permanently and when someone would like to help you or, even better fill your work because you left the company, in order to continue the development.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As well as you must respect a standard developping method to be understandable by anyone and communicate around your project. I believe that the third rules which will make you a professional is to respect the deadlines and to keep update of important news in your fields.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For example, as a professional I should return this blog today with this post !</p>\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span>\n\nGlobal informations, from ccSkills - <a href=\"https://ccskills.org.uk/careers/blog/being-a-creative-professional\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Being a creative professional</a>\n\nGlobal informations, from the context of things\'s Blog - <a href=\"http://thecontextofthings.com/2016/03/07/professionalism-in-the-workplace/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Professionalism in the workplace</a>\n\nEthic, from ethical systems - <a href=\"http://ethicalsystems.org/content/professionalism_and_ethics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Professionalsim and ethics</a>\n\nTips to become a professional, from tech republic\'s Blog - <a href=\"http://www.techrepublic.com/blog/10-things/10-things-that-define-a-true-professional/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">10 things that define a true professional</a>', 'Does the concept of professionalism apply to the creative industries ?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'does-the-concept-of-professionalism-apply-to-the-creative-industries', '', '\nhttp://thecontextofthings.com/2016/03/07/professionalism-in-the-workplace/', '2019-11-27 11:03:03', '2019-11-27 11:03:03', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/blog/?p=302', 0, 'post', '', 0),
