d rules which will make you a professional is to respect the deadlines.\r\n\r\nFor example, as a professional I should return this blog today with this post !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span>\r\n\r\nGlobal informations, from ccSkills - <a href=\"https://ccskills.org.uk/careers/blog/being-a-creative-professional\" target=\"_blank\">Being a creative professional</a>\r\n\r\nGlobal informations, from the context of things\'s Blog - <a href=\"http://thecontextofthings.com/2016/03/07/professionalism-in-the-workplace/\" target=\"_blank\">Professionalism in the workplace</a>\r\n\r\nEthic, from ethical systems - <a href=\"http://ethicalsystems.org/content/professionalism_and_ethics\" target=\"_blank\">Professionalsim and ethics</a>\r\n\r\nTips to become a professional, from tech republic\'s Blog - <a href=\"http://www.techrepublic.com/blog/10-things/10-things-that-define-a-true-professional/\" target=\"_blank\">10 things that define a true professional</a>', 'Does the concept of professionalism apply to the creative industries ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '302-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 12:16:03', '2016-10-07 11:16:03', '', 302, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/302-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(547, 1, '2019-11-27 10:48:33', '2019-11-27 10:48:33', 'Hello everyone and welcome for a new post this week,\n\nThis week I will study the question of freelancing, I will deal about pros &amp; cons and give you my opinion about it. Is it a good choice of career ?\n\nBasically we can say that freelancing is being a self-employe, that provide services to multiples customers. Be his own boss and work for the most part of the time alone, his a choice of career.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_523\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"500\"]<img class=\"wp-image-523 size-full\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/freelance3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"391\" /> A choice of career[/caption]\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As you may know, the freelancing in the EU is in good health, this numbers from the IPA are one more proof !</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #808080;\">\"Independent professionals in the EU grew from 6.2 million in 2004 to 8.9 million in 2013.The <a href=\"http://www.ipa.co.uk/page/ipa-agency-census#.V_eaeCgrI2w\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">IPA\'s 2014 Agency Census</a></span> <span style=\"color: #808080;\">revealed creative roles account for 41.8% of freelance jobs for member agencies.\"\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span> CampaignLive -</span> <a href=\"http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/1346999/why-creative-industries-embracing-freelance-economy#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">why creative industries embracing freelance economy</a></p>\n\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_524\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"1024\"]<img class=\"wp-image-524 size-full\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/freelance4-1024x420.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"420\" /> What people believe about freelancing[/caption]\n<ul>\n 	<li>One of the most interesting advantage for freelancer, is as you work alone, you are only dependant of the customer\'s order. You  can manage as you want your time during the week.Moreover, you <span style=\"color: #000000;\">work for you because <em>you </em>are the boss here, you choose your contract with your customers.\n</span></li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">The second major advantage is that you can choose your customers, it will able you to developp your network.</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Furthermore due to the differentes orders you won\'t make the same thing all the time and you will permanently improve a variety of skills.</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">As you work alone you are more pay than in a traditional company (more fees)</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\"></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">With already this point of view with the dvantages, you trust in a dream job, but there are also cons, like in all job.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Cons :</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">As you depend of your network\'s order, you must build and maitain a decent network in order to work during all the year and get your money, there is no job security it is very important to notice that !</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">You are not alone on the freelancer market. Remember the previous statistic, it will be a real contest between freelancer for interesting call, and there is many website to find orders (freelancer.co.uk , freelanceuk.com,  peopleperhour.com, etc)</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">You will probably work more than a traditionnal job because as a boss you must provide papers for the administration</li>\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">Lonely...</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>My own point of view :</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">As you have maybe guess during this article I won\'t do a freelance, but it can be a good choice of career and the road to success in the creative industry.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">It is pretty interesting thing to be in charge and manage his own time and skill to respond at customer\'s orders. I believe that it is a great experience, but until you have a decent network it is not a reliable situation.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">So I will recomend to start a freelance when you get the network or when you have time and don\'t need a reliable situation (for your family for example).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I believe that it can be a great experience to do few years in freelancing before to comeback on the traditional work, because it will bring you another point of view of work than you collegue, and it is always interesting to have differents experiences.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>How succeed as a freelancer  in the creative industry?</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">I think in one word we can define how succeed : <strong>Professionalism</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you provide a good work as the customer expect and you are aware about your network you will be an happy and successfull creative freelancer !</p>\n\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_522\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"580\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-522\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/freelance2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"580\" height=\"349\" /> Road to success[/caption]\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Statistics, from Campaign - <a href=\"http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/article/1346999/why-creative-industries-embracing-freelance-economy#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Why creative industries embracing freelance economy</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">General informations, from CreativeSkillset - <a href=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/working-in-the-creative-industries-is-freelancing-the-road-to-success/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">What\'s it like to work in the creative industries</a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Personal view, from FastoCreate - <a href=\"https://www.fastcocreate.com/1681611/how-to-be-a-happy-and-successful-creative-freelancer-or-work-with-one\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">How to be a happy and successful creative freelancer or work with one</a></p>', 'Working in the creative industries: is freelancing the road to success ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '298-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-11-27 10:48:33', '2019-11-27 10:48:33', '', 298, 'http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/2019/11/27/298-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
