w more about you personality and your level.\r\n\r\nIn my opinion, a LinkedIn profile and a Portfolio are both complementary. They are incredible tools to promote your profile.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSpeaking for myself, I believe that nowadays it is impossible to find a job in our industry without this 2 features, because you will be in contest with others profiles more interesting for the employer, even if you have the best diploma.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn order to convince you of my mind, I can give you a statistic proof :\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #999999;\"><em>\"56 percent of all hiring managers are more impressed by a candidate’s online portfolio than any other personal branding tool. However, only 7 percent of job seekers have created an online portfolio.\" <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span> <a href=\"http://www.levo.com/articles/career-advice/4-reasons-you-need-an-online-portfolio\" target=\"_blank\">4 reasons you need an online portfolio</a></em></span>\r\n\r\nIs it not an incredible tool ? Furthermore, I can swear you that have a Portfolio will be more and more common in few years, it is actualy only used in some fields, and I can give you one as an example : The creative industries.\r\n\r\nHowever, I am sure if I want to work in my country (France) and I haven\'t an enought decent Portfolio or a developed network, even if there are important studios (I think especially at EA, Ubisoft,...) I am sure I will stay without any job !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>So how make a decent Portfolio ?</strong>\r\n\r\nAfter studying the differents sources, I can give you a shortlist of advices :\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Describe your old projects</li>\r\n 	<li>Update it regulary, you should give information about your work in progress</li>\r\n 	<li>Show your skills, you must impress the visitor of your website (I believe, that even if it is a complicated to do, add a showreel update showreel of your skills is the best thing you can do to enhance your profile)</li>\r\n 	<li>Promote it, however nobody will come to check your profile !</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo conclude this post, I will compare 2 Portfolio. The <a href=\"http://www.adhamdannaway.com/\">first one </a>belongs to <a href=\"https://au.linkedin.com/in/adhamdannaway/\">Adham Dannaway</a> it is a perfect demonstration of what should be a Portfolio for me. For the second, I will share you<a style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\" href=\"http://geetix.net\"> a friend\'s Portfolio</a>. I would like to show you that even if his website looks good, it is not a decent Portfolio to promote your profile, because there is nothing about his project or his experience  ! Could you guess he have a <a style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\" href=\"https://fr.linkedin.com/in/benoit-dumas\">LinkedIn </a>or he had a <a style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\" href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20151202174954/http://geetix.net/blog/\">blog in the past</a> ?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThat\'s why it is important to keep his Portfolio update until he become useless and doesn\'t deserve you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHope you enjoyed this post, and as I told you about the importance of a Portfolio, you will find <a href=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/EN/\">mine </a>in a near future with my older project and this blog project !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source:  </span>\r\n\r\nPorfolio definition - from College of Charleston, <a href=\"http://careercenter.cofc.edu/documents/portfolio.pdf\">Career center document</a>\r\n\r\nImpact of a Portfolio for job seekers - from Levo ,  <a href=\"http://www.levo.com/articles/career-advice/4-reasons-you-need-an-online-portfolio\" target=\"_blank\">4 reasons you need an online portfolio</a>\r\n\r\nWhy a website is required - from Forbes, <a href=\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/jacquelynsmith/2013/04/26/why-every-job-seeker-should-have-a-personal-website-and-what-it-should-include/#6438b81b902e\" target=\"_blank\">Why every job seeker should have a personal website and what it should include</a>', 'What makes a good portfolio or showreel in the creative industries ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '275-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 15:15:18', '2016-10-07 14:15:18', '', 275, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/275-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(458, 1, '2016-10-07 15:16:51', '2016-10-07 14:16:51', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-319 aligncenter\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/mmm.jpg\" alt=\"mmm\" width=\"275\" height=\"183\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHey, my name is Vincent, I am a 20 years old french student. I am currently studying Game Development in the University of the West of Scotland (UWS), and I wish you the welcome on my blog !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #993366; text-decoration: underline;\">About me\r\n</span></span></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"wp-image-320 alignleft\" src=\"http://127.0.0.1/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/IMG_20160924_161106-2.jpg\" alt=\"img_20160924_161106-2\" width=\"504\" height=\"283\" /> For 8 years, computing and video games have taken an important part on my free time. First of all, I have started as a self-educated and I did many projects to discover deeper the computing field.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">That\'s why, I decided to continue my studies in a first time in Electrical Engineering &amp; Industrial Computing during 2 years, in order to discover fields like automations, electronic, embeded computing which were fields that interested myself.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Finaly, I decided to forward in the computing. Instead of chose directly a french engineering school, I have prefered to take this year in a foreign country, in order to improve my english which is a very important skill in this field and also in the profesional world.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Moreover, I believe that this experience to discover an other culture, way of work, lifestyle, and also one of the interesting specifities of computing (Game Development) is a great opportunity\r\nfor me. Furthermore, I am sure about that this experience will help in my project of study after this year.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #993366; text-decoration: underline;\">About the blog</span></span></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis blog has been designed to cover various topics associated with ethical and professional aspects of the creative industries, In a first time, I will deal with subjects submitted during the Creative Technology Profesionalism course as creative industries, game design and related subjects.\r\nMoreover, in the future, I would like to publish other topics close to this fields !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFeel free to add me on your social account !\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '264-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 15:16:51', '2016-10-07 14:16:51', '', 264, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/264-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(459, 1, '2016-10-07 15:19:14', '2016-10-07 14:19:14', 'Hello everyone to my second post.\r\n\r\nIn this new post, I will in a first time deal about the Intelectual Property (IP) and then we will focusing more on IP rights in the creative industry.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFirst of all, let\'s introduce a short definition of IP rights from the<a href=\"http://www.wipo.int/edocs/pubdocs/en/intproperty/450/wipo_pub_450.pdf\"> World Intellectual Property Organization  (WIPO)</a> :<img class=\"alignright wp-image-415\" title=\"It was your idea ?\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/intellectual-property.jpg\" alt=\"intellectual-property\" width=\"223\" height=\"192\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #999999;\">\r\n\"Intellectual property refers to creations of the mind: inventions; literary and artistic works; and symbols, names and images used in commerce. Intellectual property is divided into two categories: Industrial property and Copyright\"</span></p>\r\nIn this quote, the WIPO define the IP to all kind of creations of the mind, it can be a right on a car model (industrial property) as well as  music (copyright), so it can be applied at a wide range of industry.\r\n\r\nThe aim of IP rights are like any other property right : They allow creators, or owners, of patents, trademarks or copyrighted works to prevent from a exploitation of the invention by a person or a company.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_417\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"480\"]<img class=\"wp-image-417 size-full\" title=\"We have all already see this screen !\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/hqdefault-1-e1475832042946.jpg\" alt=\"We have all already see this screen !\" width=\"480\" height=\"266\" /> Youtube - Copyright claim[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-413\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Microsoft-Office-VS-LibreOffice.jpg\" alt=\"microsoft-office-vs-libreoffice\" width=\"110\" height=\"110\" />\r\nThis right is recognized  since 1883 and it has been established in order to give at the creator the benefit from their own work or investment in a creation. It able to the inventor to sell his rigth, deliver licences (you pay for a service) or even to get royalties !\r\nWhereas at the opposite there is also open source creation which will avoid this right and provide this service free for you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHowever, even if you are the author or creator of a new creation, you are not obviously the owner !\r\nFor example if I create a new ingenious game mechanic, if I work for a game development company, this company will be the owner of the right. So we can say that the IP rights able to prevent also company from their own employee.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNow I will deal more in details with the copyright since it will more interest us in the creative industry. The copyright covers creative fields as music, movies, art, web content, photography and others. This right is automatically obtained when you write: the copyright symbol, your name and the year on a original creation and it will protect your work in your country but also at the international. Moreover you can assert your right up to 70 years after you died (<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/copyright/how-long-copyright-lasts\">depending of the kind of creations</a>), that\'s how if you are the son of Mickael Jackson you will  still <a href=\"https://johnsonsrambler.wordpress.com/2010/04/13/a-deeper-look-at-how-much-musicians-make-online/\">receive money from his creation </a>!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn my opinion, I believe that in the creative industry the copyright is a means to push the inovation. Creativity is what will able you to overcome the current limits and design a new concept. In this way, you will probably pass this limit and maybe create an awesome creation which will maybe become the new reference.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-414\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/counter-strike-source-m4a1-silver-e1475832462841.jpg\" alt=\"counter-strike-source-m4a1-silver\" width=\"402\" height=\"153\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEven if sometimes the copyright of other will cost or block you in your project, you can always find a new way to do it. I remember an old version of Counter Strike (Source) in which Valve hadn\'t the rights on weapon\'s name yet. So they decided to \"create\" they own weapons which were just similar to the real weapons and create names (Maverick M4A1 Carabine instead of M4A1), smart ?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo conclude I will say that in the creative industry and more usually in all industry the Intelectual Property rights able to overcome the current limit. Even if it will be interesting I i think that a world with only open source invention without IP rights is not reliable for the invention. I believe that it will be the death of inovation because we will all adopt the same technology, so yes there is bad and good on IP rights but it is necessary to prevent the work provided and for the inovation !\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-418 aligncenter\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Dessin_-_01.jpg\" alt=\"dessin_-_01\" width=\"478\" height=\"350\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span>\r\n\r\nGlobal informations, from Wipo (World Intellectual Property Organization) <a href=\"http://www.wipo.int/edocs/pubdocs/en/intproperty/450/wipo_pub_450.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">- What is intelectual property</a>\r\n\r\nGlobal information, from Innovation policy platform <a href=\"https://www.innovationpolicyplatform.org/content/ip-and-creative-industries\" target=\"_blank\"> IP and creative industry</a>\r\n\r\nCopyright/Copyleft, from visionmobile blog <a href=\"https://www.visionmobile.com/blog/2011/03/the-open-source-trials-hanging-in-the-legal-balance-of-copyright-and-copyleft\" target=\"_blank\"> The open source trials hanging in the legal balance of copyright and copyleft</a>\r\n\r\nCopyright in the UK, from the UK government <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/copyright/overview\" target=\"_blank\"> How copyright protects your work</a>\r\n\r\nMusic royalties, from  Johnsons Rambler blog <a href=\"https://johnsonsrambler.wordpress.com/2010/04/13/a-deeper-look-at-how-much-musicians-make-online/\" target=\"_blank\"> A deeper look at how much musicians make online</a>', 'Intelectual Property rights and their importance in the creative industries', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '300-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 15:19:14', '2016-10-07 14:19:14', '', 300, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/300-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(553, 1, '2019-11-27 11:03:03', '2019-11-27 11:03:03', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hello everyone to this new post,</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Today I will deal about Profesionalism, especially in the creative industry. If you have already work in a company, this word won\'t be strange for you, but for most of student they can\'t define Professionalism, so I want to show you on image what is the profesionalism :</p>\n\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_531\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1000\"]<img class=\"wp-image-531 size-full\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/professionalism_1000-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"622\" /> This guy seems professional[/caption]\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Personaly, the first word in mind when I pronounce \"Professionalism\" are : reliable, discipline, serving, competent. I think I will define a professional as a person who will bring what his customer desire, or even more, in the best way.</p>\n<strong>Why do I need to be professional ?</strong>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">If you need to work in a important company, you can\'t go to work and want to be yourself, because once you are yourself you are  naturally unprofessional.\nIn order to work in good terms and in the good way you need to adopt professional codes, which will depends of your field.</p>\n<strong>Identify a professional person</strong>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_532\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"300\"]<img class=\"wp-image-532 size-full\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/ProfessionalCircles.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"268\" /> Professionalism Diagram[/caption]\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">I have found this image on one of my source, and I think it is a good diagram to define how you can begin a professional.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We can see that the professionalism is a melt beetween : behaviour, skills, knowledge.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Obviously if you want to provide a good work to your customers you shoud have a decent skillset and knowledge, depending on your field.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although in my opinion I believe that behaviour is what will be differencing you as a professional and from your teammates. Because, theoretically you will have an equivalent level in technicals skills due to the fact that you are working on the same field. It will impact your communication and  your role wihin the group.</p>\n<strong>Professionalism in the creative industry</strong>\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_533\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"400\"]<img class=\"wp-image-533 size-full\" src=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Robots-in-Suits.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\" /> Robots in suits[/caption]\n\nFirst of all, to be a professional you must respect the codes of your field.\n\nWhereas in buisness, restoration or even in some school you must wear a kind of uniform to work. In the creative industry, I can  say that it is more creative, there is not a defined clothing code !\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">However for the work providden by developper the professionalism is a really important. When you are working in a company, you probably won\'t be alone on your project, that\'s why communication will be very important.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Althought, there is not only the oral communication, as a developper your codes must be first of all reliable and understandable by any others developpers. They should be able to understand your codes, mainly because a computing project is updated permanently and when someone would like to help you or, even better fill your work because you left the company, in order to continue the development.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">As well as you must respect a standard developping method to be understandable by anyone and communicate around your project. I believe that the third rules which will make you a professional is to respect the deadlines and to keep update of important news in your fields.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For example, as a professional I should return this blog today with this post !</p>\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span>\n\nGlobal informations, from ccSkills - <a href=\"https://ccskills.org.uk/careers/blog/being-a-creative-professional\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Being a creative professional</a>\n\nGlobal informations, from the context of things\'s Blog - <a href=\"http://thecontextofthings.com/2016/03/07/professionalism-in-the-workplace/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Professionalism in the workplace</a>\n\nEthic, from ethical systems - <a href=\"http://ethicalsystems.org/content/professionalism_and_ethics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Professionalsim and ethics</a>\n\nTips to become a professional, from tech republic\'s Blog - <a href=\"http://www.techrepublic.com/blog/10-things/10-things-that-define-a-true-professional/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">10 things that define a true professional</a>', 'Does the concept of professionalism apply to the creative industries ?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '302-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-11-27 11:03:03', '2019-11-27 11:03:03', '', 302, 'http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/2019/11/27/302-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(460, 1, '2016-10-07 15:23:09', '2016-10-07 14:23:09', 'Hello everyone to my second post.\r\n\r\nIn this new post, I will in a first time deal about the Intelectual Property (IP) and then we will focusing more on IP rights in the creative industry.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFirst of all, let\'s introduce a short definition of IP rights from the<a href=\"http://www.wipo.int/edocs/pubdocs/en/intproperty/450/wipo_pub_450.pdf\"> World Intellectual Property Organization  (WIPO)</a> :<img class=\"alignright wp-image-415\" title=\"It was your idea ?\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/intellectual-property.jpg\" alt=\"intellectual-property\" width=\"223\" height=\"192\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #999999;\">\r\n\"Intellectual property refers to creations of the mind: inventions; literary and artistic works; and symbols, names and images used in commerce. Intellectual property is divided into two categories: Industrial property and Copyright\"</span></p>\r\nIn this quote, the WIPO define the IP to all kind of creations of the mind, it can be a right on a car model (industrial property) as well as a music (copyright), so it can be applied at a wide range of industry.\r\n\r\nThe aim of IP rights are like any other property right : They allow creators, or owners, of patents, trademarks or copyrighted works to prevent from a exploitation of the invention by a person or a company.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_417\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"480\"]<img class=\"wp-image-417 size-full\" title=\"We have all already see this screen !\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/hqdefault-1-e1475832042946.jpg\" alt=\"We have all already see this screen !\" width=\"480\" height=\"266\" /> Youtube - Copyright claim[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-413\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Microsoft-Office-VS-LibreOffice.jpg\" alt=\"microsoft-office-vs-libreoffice\" width=\"110\" height=\"110\" />\r\nThis right is recognized  since 1883 and it has been established in order to give at the creator the benefit from their own work or investment in a creation. It able to the inventor to sell his rights, deliver licences (you pay for a service) or even to get royalties !\r\nWhereas at the opposite there are also open source creations which will avoid this righst and provide this services free for you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHowever, even if you are the author or creator of a new creation, you are not obviously the owner !\r\nFor example if I create a new ingenious game mechanic, if I work for a game development company, this company will be the owner of the right. So we can say that the IP rights able to prevent also company from their own employee.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNow I will deal more in details with the copyright since it will more interest us in the creative industry. The copyright covers creative fields as music, movies, art, web content, photography and others. This right is automatically obtained when you write: the copyright symbol, your name and the year on a original creation and it will protect your work in your country but also at the international. Moreover you can assert your right up to 70 years after you died (<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/copyright/how-long-copyright-lasts\">depending of the kind of creations</a>), that\'s how if you are the son of Mickael Jackson you will  still <a href=\"https://johnsonsrambler.wordpress.com/2010/04/13/a-deeper-look-at-how-much-musicians-make-online/\">receive money from his creation </a>!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn my opinion, I believe that in the creative industry the copyright is a means to push the inovation. Creativity is what will able you to overcome the current limits and design a new concept. In this way, you will probably pass this limit and maybe create an awesome creation which will maybe become the new reference.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-414\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/counter-strike-source-m4a1-silver-e1475832462841.jpg\" alt=\"counter-strike-source-m4a1-silver\" width=\"402\" height=\"153\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEven if sometimes the copyright of other will cost or block you in your project, you can always find a new way to do it. I remember an old version of Counter Strike (Source) in which Valve hadn\'t the rights on weapon\'s name yet. So they decided to \"create\" they own weapons which were just similar to the real weapons and create names (Maverick M4A1 Carabine instead of M4A1), smart ?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo conclude I will say that in the creative industry and more usually in all industry the Intelectual Property rights able to overcome the current limit. Even if it will be interesting I i think that a world with only open source invention without IP rights is not reliable for the invention. I believe that it will be the death of inovation because we will all adopt the same technology, so yes there is bad and good on IP rights but it is necessary to prevent the work provided and for the inovation !\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-418 aligncenter\" src=\"http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Dessin_-_01.jpg\" alt=\"dessin_-_01\" width=\"478\" height=\"350\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Source :</span>\r\n\r\nGlobal informations, from Wipo (World Intellectual Property Organization) <a href=\"http://www.wipo.int/edocs/pubdocs/en/intproperty/450/wipo_pub_450.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">- What is intelectual property</a>\r\n\r\nGlobal information, from Innovation policy platform <a href=\"https://www.innovationpolicyplatform.org/content/ip-and-creative-industries\" target=\"_blank\"> IP and creative industry</a>\r\n\r\nCopyright/Copyleft, from visionmobile blog <a href=\"https://www.visionmobile.com/blog/2011/03/the-open-source-trials-hanging-in-the-legal-balance-of-copyright-and-copyleft\" target=\"_blank\"> The open source trials hanging in the legal balance of copyright and copyleft</a>\r\n\r\nCopyright in the UK, from the UK government <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/copyright/overview\" target=\"_blank\"> How copyright protects your work</a>\r\n\r\nMusic royalties, from  Johnsons Rambler blog <a href=\"https://johnsonsrambler.wordpress.com/2010/04/13/a-deeper-look-at-how-much-musicians-make-online/\" target=\"_blank\"> A deeper look at how much musicians make online</a>', 'Intelectual Property rights and their importance in the creative industries', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '300-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 15:23:09', '2016-10-07 14:23:09', '', 300, 'http://vincent-berthet.net/en/blog/300-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(541, 1, '2019-11-27 10:36:06', '2019-11-27 10:36:06', '<p>As an other assessment for this module, I have also study more in details a subject of the creative industry in order to write a complete technical report around it.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>You can find my <strong>Technical Report</strong> dealing about the<strong> Impact of social, casual and mobile game in the evolving games industry</strong> <a href=\"http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/CA2_B00313298.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">right there</a></p>\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Technical Report : Impact of social, casual and mobile games in the evolving games', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '489-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-11-27 10:36:06', '2019-11-27 10:36:06', '', 489, 'http://uwsblog.yo.fr/UWS_Blog/2019/11/27/489-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
